SIMPLE: tyrian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tyrian
<hw>Tyr"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Tyrius</ets>, from <ets>Tyrus</ets> Tyre, Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to Tyre or its people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Being of the color called Tyrian purple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bright-eyed perch with fins of <qex>Tyrian</qex> dye.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Tyrian purple</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Tyrian
dye</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a celebrated purple dye prepared in ancient
<geog>Tyre</geog> from several mollusks, especially Ianthina, Murex, and
Purpura. See the Note under <er>Purple</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1, and
<cref>Purple of mollusca</cref>, under <er>Purple</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tyrian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tyrian
<hw>Tyr"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Tyrius</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A native of Tyre.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tyro</ent>⟦br⟧
